despite the severity of the crash

such as when hitting debris on the road

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with airbag sensors can lead to failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash, or unnecessary deployment, resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shutting off can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

the vehicle idles and shuts off without warning
especially when coming to a stop or on a slight incline.

Unusual engine noises can indicate underlying engine problems, which can lead to engine failure, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: noise from the engine at speeds of 40-50 mph.
